This paper deals with forecasting future human actions from video data, which is a problem commonly studied in computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of neural machine translation techniques and encoder-decoder architecture suggests that this paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG). The application of this method to assistive robotics and video surveillance suggests that it may also be relevant to the sub-category of robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the use of loss functions and evaluation metrics suggests that this paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of natural language processing (cs.CL).
